# No material-icons-extended

The `androidx.compose.material:material-icons-extended` library is deprecated and must not be used.

- Never add `material-icons-extended` as a dependency in any `build.gradle.kts` or `libs.versions.toml`.
- Never import from `androidx.compose.material.icons` (e.g. `Icons.Outlined.*`, `Icons.Filled.*`).
- Instead, use vector drawable XML resources in `res/drawable/` and load them with `painterResource(R.drawable.ic_*)`.

```kotlin
// BAD
import androidx.compose.material.icons.Icons
import androidx.compose.material.icons.outlined.Refresh

Icon(imageVector = Icons.Outlined.Refresh, contentDescription = null)

// GOOD
import androidx.compose.ui.res.painterResource

Icon(painter = painterResource(R.drawable.ic_refresh), contentDescription = null)
```
